On National Teacher Day, the article recognizes the dedication of teachers who instill character, integrity, and knowledge in students. It acknowledges that the coronavirus outbreak has tested traditional educational models, forcing teachers to adapt and provide instruction through innovative means. Teachers have risen to the challenge by developing creative strategies to bring their classrooms and lesson plans into students' homes. Parents and caregivers have also taken on new educational roles during this time. The article highlights the importance of ensuring that teachers have the resources they need to deliver high-quality education. The CARES Act, signed into law in March, includes over $13 billion to support K-12 teachers in providing remote learning. The article emphasizes that teachers shape the minds of children, strengthen communities, and develop future leaders.